🔹 **Document 3: SaaS Integration Security Standard & Compliance Report**
- **Filename**: `SEC-010_SaaS_Integration_Security_Standard_v4.0.pdf`
- **Content**:
  ```
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  CLOUDNEXUS MSP - SAAS INTEGRATION SECURITY STANDARD
  Document ID: SEC-STD-010 | Version 4.0 | Classification: Internal
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  1. PURPOSE & SCOPE
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  This standard mandates the use of IAM Roles with External IDs for all 
  third-party SaaS tools and internal CloudNexus platforms requiring access 
  to customer AWS accounts.

  2. MANDATORY REQUIREMENTS
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  2.1 Cross-Account Access Method
      ✓ REQUIRED: IAM Roles with sts:AssumeRole
      ✗ PROHIBITED: IAM Users, Access Keys, or hardcoded credentials

  2.2 External ID Implementation
      ✓ All trust policies MUST include sts:ExternalId condition
      ✓ External IDs must be unique per customer-tool combination
      ✓ External IDs must be minimum 16 characters
      ✓ External IDs must not be guessable or sequential

  2.3 External ID Generation Standards
      ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
      │ Source          │ Generation Method          │ Example              │
      ├─────────────────┼────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
      │ Third-Party     │ Vendor-provided via        │ dd-ext-7f3a9b2c...   │
      │ SaaS            │ integration wizard         │                      │
      ├─────────────────┼────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
      │ Internal Tools  │ CloudNexus ID Generator    │ CUST-XXXX-TOOL-      │
      │                 │ (UUID v4 + Customer ID)    │ {UUID}               │
      └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  3. CURRENT COMPLIANCE STATUS (Q4 2024)
